  <bioghist id="aspace_1664ca716159d058bb3a2a732d687de8">
    <head>Biographical Note</head>
<p>Herbert Hoeger (1924-2014) was born in the Czech Republic in an area previously identified as Austria. In 1942, he was drafted into the German Army, captured by the U.S., then placed in various POW camps located in Europe and the United States. He was discharged from the army in 1946, attended college in Vienna, and immigrated to the United States in 1957. He became a U.S. citizen in 1978. Hoeger lived mostly in New York City and Warrensburg, New York. He worked as a lab technician for a dairy and was a model for print ads.</p>  </bioghist>
